1
00:00:05,741 --> 00:00:07,271
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:09,011
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,441 --> 00:00:12,181
(Episode 32)

4
00:00:13,681 --> 00:00:15,551
I'm glad her surgery went well.

5
00:00:19,991 --> 00:00:21,051
Are you leaving...

6
00:00:21,821 --> 00:00:23,091
because of me?

7
00:00:23,891 --> 00:00:24,921
I know I promised...

8
00:00:26,391 --> 00:00:28,701
to always be here for you.

9
00:00:30,231 --> 00:00:31,701
And I'm sorry...

10
00:00:32,931 --> 00:00:33,971
that I'm leaving.

11
00:00:35,071 --> 00:00:36,071
You just...

12
00:00:36,601 --> 00:00:38,101
can't bear to see me anymore?

13
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:45,011
I just...

14
00:00:46,051 --> 00:00:49,051
care about your mother
and grandmother too much.

15
00:00:51,081 --> 00:00:52,421
I can't risk...

16
00:00:53,651 --> 00:00:54,851
hurting them anymore.

17
00:01:02,631 --> 00:01:03,661
Can we...

18
00:01:04,831 --> 00:01:06,401
have one last...

19
00:01:07,431 --> 00:01:08,501
hug?

20
00:01:45,911 --> 00:01:48,641
(Intensive Care Unit)

21
00:01:54,181 --> 00:01:56,021
She'll be waking up soon.
All her vitals are normal.

22
00:01:56,451 --> 00:01:58,021
Okay, thank you.

23
00:02:02,921 --> 00:02:03,961
What did she say, Grandma?

24
00:02:04,291 --> 00:02:07,591
She said she's fine.
Her breathing and vitals are stable.

25
00:02:08,731 --> 00:02:10,131
That's such a relief.

26
00:02:10,601 --> 00:02:11,961
So, what's this?

27
00:02:13,001 --> 00:02:14,501
Oh, this.

28
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:18,101
Well, Director Yang was just here.

29
00:02:22,181 --> 00:02:23,311
We said our goodbyes.

30
00:02:24,541 --> 00:02:26,651
He's going back to Argentina,
I hear?

31
00:02:28,211 --> 00:02:30,221
So you already knew, Grandma.

32
00:02:32,421 --> 00:02:36,221
It's for the best.
I'll just focus on Mom getting well.

33
00:02:41,961 --> 00:02:43,261
- Mom.
- Oh, my.

34
00:02:46,231 --> 00:02:47,731
Seong Mi, are you okay?

35
00:02:49,201 --> 00:02:51,501
- Mother.
- Yes, I'm here.

36
00:02:54,141 --> 00:02:58,481
- It went well, didn't it?
- It did. You did great, Mom.

37
00:02:58,851 --> 00:03:00,251
You've been through so much,
Seong Mi.

38
00:03:00,781 --> 00:03:04,081
- Ju Ah, go call your dad.
- Right.

39
00:03:06,121 --> 00:03:07,121
Are you in pain?

40
00:03:07,591 --> 00:03:08,591
No...

41
00:03:18,131 --> 00:03:21,471
Isn't this Veronica's phone?

42
00:03:21,531 --> 00:03:23,871
This is her mom.

43
00:03:24,141 --> 00:03:25,741
Veronica?

44
00:03:32,011 --> 00:03:33,311
It can't be.

45
00:03:34,751 --> 00:03:36,281
My gosh, this is so cute.

46
00:03:36,781 --> 00:03:37,851
What's this?

47
00:03:38,251 --> 00:03:39,821
It's a picture of me
when I was a baby.

48
00:03:52,131 --> 00:03:53,271
I'm back.

49
00:03:56,471 --> 00:04:00,271
- Did you buy us a snack?
- Yes, sticky rice doughnuts.

50
00:04:00,411 --> 00:04:04,641
A shop out front makes them
to order, and they're so good.

51
00:04:05,241 --> 00:04:07,711
I see. Nice.

52
00:04:07,711 --> 00:04:10,721
- All right. Let's eat.
- Okay.

53
00:04:20,531 --> 00:04:22,731
- Hey, Min Seo.
- Yes?

54
00:04:22,861 --> 00:04:24,801
You should give your mom a call.

55
00:04:25,031 --> 00:04:26,031
Pardon me?

56
00:04:26,231 --> 00:04:30,401
She just called.
I figured she would worry,

57
00:04:30,471 --> 00:04:31,771
so I picked it up.

58
00:04:31,841 --> 00:04:36,211
Really? Thank you. I was so hungry,

59
00:04:36,281 --> 00:04:38,041
I didn't even realize
I'd left my phone.

60
00:04:40,151 --> 00:04:42,581
By any chance,

61
00:04:45,951 --> 00:04:47,191
is your English name...

62
00:04:48,291 --> 00:04:49,521
Veronica?

63
00:04:52,261 --> 00:04:54,191
Well, yes.

64
00:04:55,801 --> 00:04:57,431
That's a very beautiful name.

65
00:04:58,971 --> 00:05:00,531
Who gave it to you?

66
00:05:02,901 --> 00:05:05,941
Well, my mom did.

67
00:05:06,811 --> 00:05:10,911
She was a fan of an actress named
Veronica Ethereal Wind.

68
00:05:12,041 --> 00:05:14,381
I see.

69
00:05:14,611 --> 00:05:17,151
Yes, it's a pretty common name
in the US.

70
00:05:18,881 --> 00:05:20,691
- Go on, have some.
- Okay.

71
00:05:30,101 --> 00:05:32,831
(Dr. Han Seong Mi
Temporarily Halts Work for Health)

72
00:05:32,901 --> 00:05:35,271
Woo Jae must be having
such a hard time.

73
00:05:36,571 --> 00:05:38,101
Should I call him?

74
00:05:39,011 --> 00:05:41,471
No. I need to be strong,
especially at a time like this.

75
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,881
Right. I decided
to focus on what I want.

76
00:05:46,311 --> 00:05:49,281
Hey, Min Seo. How is it,
being alone with your mom?

77
00:05:49,281 --> 00:05:50,281
(3H Acupressure Bed)

78
00:05:50,281 --> 00:05:54,891
Eun Bin, Mom found out
that my English name is Veronica.

79
00:05:55,421 --> 00:05:58,021
What? How did that happen?

80
00:05:58,661 --> 00:06:00,631
I stepped out without my phone,

81
00:06:00,631 --> 00:06:02,461
and she answered a call
from my mom back in the US.

82
00:06:02,861 --> 00:06:05,731
Wait, really?
And she only found out the name?

83
00:06:05,801 --> 00:06:06,871
Nothing else?

84
00:06:07,631 --> 00:06:12,241
Yes, I think so. She just asked
who gave me the name.

85
00:06:14,141 --> 00:06:15,141
That's a relief.

86
00:06:15,781 --> 00:06:18,441
Hey, listen.
I gave Mom those papers.

87
00:06:18,681 --> 00:06:20,581
Papers? What papers?

88
00:06:21,711 --> 00:06:25,751
Okay. I'll look for them.
We can't let her find out.

89
00:06:26,051 --> 00:06:28,051
If Mom finds out,
she'll give it away,

90
00:06:28,051 --> 00:06:30,491
and if Dad finds out, it's all over.

91
00:06:35,691 --> 00:06:36,701
Hold on.

92
00:06:37,361 --> 00:06:39,301
What did you just say?

93
00:06:39,601 --> 00:06:43,471
A child... She had a child?

94
00:06:44,971 --> 00:06:45,971
My Se Ri?

95
00:06:47,571 --> 00:06:50,681
- You didn't know. What have I done?
- No, wait.

96
00:06:51,741 --> 00:06:53,851
Are you sure you're not mistaken?

97
00:06:53,951 --> 00:06:56,381
- No, it's just that...
- Is it true?

98
00:06:58,151 --> 00:06:59,521
Did my Se Ri really...

99
00:07:01,351 --> 00:07:02,691
have a child?

100
00:07:05,521 --> 00:07:07,191
It seems you only knew
half the story.

101
00:07:08,631 --> 00:07:09,761
So, then...

102
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:13,771
- You're saying she was married?
- No.

103
00:07:14,171 --> 00:07:17,401
She wasn't married.
At the convent's orphanage,

104
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:20,111
she met a guy. What was his name?

105
00:07:20,171 --> 00:07:23,581
Yes, Oh Jong Gil.
They dated, and she got pregnant.

106
00:07:23,681 --> 00:07:27,151
But right before she gave birth,
he died.

107
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:32,221
She put the baby up for adoption
through the agency at the convent,

108
00:07:33,651 --> 00:07:36,891
and that's when she met you.

109
00:07:37,961 --> 00:07:40,631
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

110
00:07:44,201 --> 00:07:46,031
(Wifey)

111
00:07:46,101 --> 00:07:48,801
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

112
00:07:50,671 --> 00:07:54,411
- Hey, Se Ri.
- Honey, are you picking me up?

113
00:07:54,711 --> 00:07:57,881
Actually,
I have dinner plans tonight.

114
00:07:58,941 --> 00:07:59,951
Right.

115
00:08:01,211 --> 00:08:02,211
Get home safe.

116
00:08:19,301 --> 00:08:20,501
You're back.

117
00:08:23,801 --> 00:08:25,971
My gosh,
what's that delicious smell?

118
00:08:26,041 --> 00:08:28,871
I made braised kimchi with pork.
Grandfather and I already ate.

119
00:08:28,941 --> 00:08:30,981
And it was so good,
even if I do say so myself.

120
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:33,911
Maybe that's because
Mom's kimchi is so good?

121
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:36,151
That's correct! You got it!

122
00:08:36,721 --> 00:08:38,751
I'm going to get changed
and try some.

123
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:47,231
What? Where did Min Seo's papers go?

124
00:08:48,391 --> 00:08:50,501
I'm sure I put them right here.

125
00:08:58,201 --> 00:08:59,211
That's strange.

126
00:09:06,181 --> 00:09:09,351
- Did you find the papers?
- Of course, I did.

127
00:09:09,421 --> 00:09:12,351
Your ID card and visa copy,
the ones in Mom's vanity drawer.

128
00:09:12,421 --> 00:09:13,791
I found them and hid them.

129
00:09:14,091 --> 00:09:17,321
Thank goodness.
My full date of birth is on there.

130
00:09:17,491 --> 00:09:20,661
- You have to be so careful, right?
- Yes.

131
00:09:30,801 --> 00:09:34,411
There's one more person
I need to see before I go back.

132
00:09:38,181 --> 00:09:42,881
I'm free anytime.
Whenever works for you, Sister.

133
00:09:45,481 --> 00:09:46,491
She clearly...

134
00:09:47,751 --> 00:09:49,761
She clearly said, "Sister."

135
00:09:50,721 --> 00:09:55,231
But what if... What if Veronica...

136
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:58,031
asked for your number?

137
00:10:18,581 --> 00:10:19,591
No way.

138
00:10:21,891 --> 00:10:26,261
No, that's impossible.
No, this is crazy.

139
00:10:32,531 --> 00:10:34,071
Do you want some water?

140
00:10:34,471 --> 00:10:36,501
I haven't had any yet.
Do you want it?

141
00:10:36,941 --> 00:10:38,801
No, I'll get my own.

142
00:10:39,071 --> 00:10:40,071
Okay.

143
00:10:42,611 --> 00:10:43,611
Min Seo.

144
00:10:44,511 --> 00:10:45,511
Yes?

145
00:10:46,681 --> 00:10:49,081
By any chance,
when is your birthday?

146
00:10:49,951 --> 00:10:52,821
Oh, August 7.

147
00:10:53,651 --> 00:10:55,121
Why do you ask?

148
00:10:55,691 --> 00:11:00,631
I thought I'd get you something
if it's during your visit.

149
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:01,991
I see.

150
00:11:02,131 --> 00:11:03,401
That's a shame.

151
00:11:22,921 --> 00:11:27,391
What if people from my past
recognize me when the show airs?

152
00:11:28,191 --> 00:11:29,191
Why?

153
00:11:29,521 --> 00:11:33,031
Did someone leave a comment?
Did they write my real name?

154
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:54,451
Hey, how are you feeling?

155
00:11:57,181 --> 00:11:58,651
I'm holding up.

156
00:11:59,151 --> 00:12:03,461
Maybe it's the painkillers,
but the pain is manageable.

157
00:12:03,521 --> 00:12:07,061
Come on. They just cut you open.

158
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:10,001
If it hurts, tell me.
Don't just hold it in.

159
00:12:10,901 --> 00:12:11,901
Okay.

160
00:12:12,531 --> 00:12:15,531
You should have had Jeong Han come
so you could rest at home.

161
00:12:15,531 --> 00:12:19,711
Nonsense, I wanted to stay.
It was hard getting Ju Ah to leave.

162
00:12:19,811 --> 00:12:23,241
Ju Ah has to work,
so she needs her rest.

163
00:12:23,311 --> 00:12:25,841
Yes. And later,

164
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:28,011
I heard Woo Jae's coming by
after work too.

165
00:12:28,211 --> 00:12:30,881
Gosh, everyone's making such a fuss.

166
00:12:33,521 --> 00:12:36,161
By the way,
did someone stop by earlier?

167
00:12:37,061 --> 00:12:39,531
Oh, that...

168
00:12:39,991 --> 00:12:43,931
Director Yang stopped by earlier.
He left that with Ju Ah for you.

169
00:12:46,501 --> 00:12:47,501
Right.

170
00:12:48,271 --> 00:12:51,171
Did you hear anything
about the fashion show's reception?

171
00:12:51,241 --> 00:12:56,041
Yes. Ju Ah showed me the articles.
There were a ton of articles.

172
00:12:57,341 --> 00:12:58,341
That's a relief.

173
00:12:59,981 --> 00:13:02,181
I'm so glad things went well
for Ju Ah, too.

174
00:13:02,781 --> 00:13:04,381
I was so against it,

175
00:13:04,721 --> 00:13:08,451
but seeing her pull it off
makes me feel sorry and so proud.

176
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:16,601
I heard Director Yang is quitting
and moving abroad.

177
00:13:16,861 --> 00:13:17,901
Is he?

178
00:13:18,661 --> 00:13:20,431
Bucket must be upset.

179
00:13:20,931 --> 00:13:22,841
He only just got back.

180
00:13:23,871 --> 00:13:24,871
I know.

181
00:13:26,141 --> 00:13:28,141
- Mother.
- Yes.

182
00:13:28,941 --> 00:13:32,041
I think Director Yang has feelings
for our Ju Ah.

183
00:13:33,711 --> 00:13:34,751
You noticed?

184
00:13:35,011 --> 00:13:39,791
More than noticed.
I told him to give up on her.

185
00:13:41,051 --> 00:13:42,051
You did?

186
00:13:42,961 --> 00:13:47,191
Director Yang is a great guy,
but his family is... You know.

187
00:13:48,331 --> 00:13:50,601
Now that Ju Ah and Jun Hyeok
have broken up,

188
00:13:50,961 --> 00:13:52,731
I was worried
she and Director Yang might start...

189
00:13:53,131 --> 00:13:55,931
developing feelings for each other
if they kept spending time together.

190
00:13:56,501 --> 00:13:59,001
So it's a good thing he's quitting.

191
00:14:01,011 --> 00:14:03,541
Do you hate his family that much?

192
00:14:05,711 --> 00:14:07,811
Just thinking about it
stresses me out.

193
00:14:07,881 --> 00:14:11,921
Don't think about it. Don't stress.
Okay? Just don't.

194
00:14:19,061 --> 00:14:21,161
What? Who is it?

195
00:14:22,161 --> 00:14:24,361
Director! It's me, Mr. Park!

196
00:14:24,831 --> 00:14:25,831
Mr. Park?

197
00:14:31,501 --> 00:14:32,501
What?

198
00:14:33,171 --> 00:14:38,111
Hey! What is this? What's going on?
Why are you barging into my place?

199
00:14:38,181 --> 00:14:40,611
Barging in?
You opened the door for me.

200
00:14:40,681 --> 00:14:43,781
I opened it since I didn't want you
to bother the neighbors.

201
00:14:44,681 --> 00:14:45,751
So, how did it go?

202
00:14:46,021 --> 00:14:48,921
- How did what go?
- You met with Ju Ah.

203
00:14:49,021 --> 00:14:50,061
I did.

204
00:14:50,921 --> 00:14:51,921
So, is it over?

205
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:54,791
- It's over.
- Darn it!

206
00:14:56,861 --> 00:14:59,031
Hey, are you annoyed with me?
I'm your director.

207
00:14:59,771 --> 00:15:01,401
You're not my director if you quit.

208
00:15:01,531 --> 00:15:05,101
Even so, let's avoid insubordination
until I'm actually gone.

209
00:15:05,441 --> 00:15:10,211
But why are you quitting? Why?
And why break it off with her? Why?

210
00:15:10,911 --> 00:15:13,411
Anyone watching would think
I'm breaking up with you.

211
00:15:13,551 --> 00:15:15,581
You are.
You're breaking up with me too.

212
00:15:15,981 --> 00:15:17,951
How can you be so irresponsible?

213
00:15:18,051 --> 00:15:22,891
What's irresponsible about this?
I got the Fashion Division on track,

214
00:15:22,991 --> 00:15:24,621
and the launch show
was a huge success.

215
00:15:27,831 --> 00:15:28,831
What? What's this?

216
00:15:29,191 --> 00:15:31,701
- You're packing already?
- I am.

217
00:15:32,201 --> 00:15:33,801
Come on! No!

218
00:15:34,331 --> 00:15:37,601
Director! You can't go!
Don't go! No!

219
00:15:38,001 --> 00:15:39,811
Gosh, you're nuts.

220
00:15:40,671 --> 00:15:44,081
- I'm going crazy! How could I not?
- Oh, come on.

221
00:15:44,141 --> 00:15:46,281
Yes, "come on" yourself.
No, you can't!

222
00:15:46,351 --> 00:15:47,751
What do you mean, no?

223
00:15:47,951 --> 00:15:50,851
And wait, be formal.
I'm your director.

224
00:15:51,281 --> 00:15:53,691
You know what? I should just go
and marry the Vice President...

225
00:15:53,751 --> 00:15:55,321
and become the son-in-law
of Taehan Group.

226
00:15:55,391 --> 00:15:57,121
Then you couldn't say a thing to me,
Director or not.

227
00:15:57,361 --> 00:15:59,691
Wow. Are you actually serious
about that?

228
00:15:59,761 --> 00:16:04,101
No, not at all. Gosh, seriously.

229
00:16:04,931 --> 00:16:08,831
Mr. Park, I know how you feel,
so just go. I'm going to bed.

230
00:16:10,401 --> 00:16:14,211
Come on, don't be like this.
Take a vacation and think it over.

231
00:16:14,571 --> 00:16:17,881
Dr. Han just had her surgery,
and Ju Ah is going through so much.

232
00:16:17,941 --> 00:16:21,681
If you break up with her now,
how am I supposed to watch her cry?

233
00:16:23,881 --> 00:16:25,051
I doubt she will.

234
00:16:29,591 --> 00:16:31,321
- I'm home!
- You scared me.

235
00:16:31,391 --> 00:16:33,231
- You scared me.
- Sorry.

236
00:16:33,431 --> 00:16:38,401
- Ju Ah, how's your mom?
- She's fine. I told you already.

237
00:16:39,431 --> 00:16:43,041
- Will she be discharged as planned?
- Yes, I think so.

238
00:16:43,241 --> 00:16:46,571
We won't know for sure
until the doctor's morning rounds.

239
00:16:46,911 --> 00:16:48,541
By the way, what are you guys doing?

240
00:16:48,711 --> 00:16:52,381
After her surgery,
she'll have trouble lifting her arm,

241
00:16:52,881 --> 00:16:55,051
so we're moving her everyday items
to lower shelves.

242
00:16:55,251 --> 00:16:58,451
And I also put a non-slip mat
in the bathroom,

243
00:16:58,751 --> 00:17:01,591
and I installed an emergency button
by her bed.

244
00:17:01,751 --> 00:17:03,821
So she can call for help
in an emergency.

245
00:17:04,861 --> 00:17:06,531
So thoughtful, Uncle.

246
00:17:07,331 --> 00:17:09,531
Ju Ah, you should go upstairs
and get some rest.

247
00:17:09,631 --> 00:17:11,761
No, it's fine.
We'll finish faster if I help.

248
00:17:12,061 --> 00:17:15,271
Hey, any word from Woo Jae yet?

249
00:17:16,071 --> 00:17:17,841
Video call from Gong Woo Jae.

250
00:17:18,401 --> 00:17:20,271
- Really?
- Yes. Quick, come here!

251
00:17:20,341 --> 00:17:21,641
- Hey!
- Hey, Gong Woo Jae!

252
00:17:22,471 --> 00:17:24,181
Hey, Ju Ah, did you make it home?

253
00:17:24,541 --> 00:17:27,311
- Dad, Uncle, I'll show you Mom.
- Okay.

254
00:17:29,751 --> 00:17:32,521
Mom, I think
Dad and Uncle are crying.

255
00:17:33,821 --> 00:17:38,421
This is too good to watch by myself.
Mother, you have to see this.

256
00:17:39,521 --> 00:17:41,861
What? Oh, my goodness.

257
00:17:42,231 --> 00:17:45,531
I swear, my sons are hopeless.
Just hopeless. Right?

258
00:17:46,801 --> 00:17:49,201
Honey, are you okay?

259
00:17:49,671 --> 00:17:52,471
Of course, I am.
And my brother-in-law?

260
00:17:52,971 --> 00:17:55,941
- Brother-in-law.
- Yes. Sister-in-law, I'm...

261
00:17:56,681 --> 00:17:59,481
- I'm okay.
- Don't you all worry.

262
00:17:59,911 --> 00:18:01,981
I'm not dead, you know.

263
00:18:02,051 --> 00:18:05,821
Why would you say a thing like that?
Honestly.

264
00:18:07,891 --> 00:18:10,221
- Gosh, Mom, don't move.
- Hey, don't laugh.

265
00:18:10,221 --> 00:18:13,291
- Stop it, you two.
- Honey, don't move.

266
00:18:13,361 --> 00:18:14,391
Don't move.

267
00:18:16,361 --> 00:18:20,701
Auntie, what about Dr. Han Seong Mi?
Did her surgery go well?

268
00:18:20,771 --> 00:18:22,901
That's right.
She would've had her surgery by now.

269
00:18:23,241 --> 00:18:25,901
Woo Jae said the surgery went well.

270
00:18:26,241 --> 00:18:27,641
That's a huge relief.

271
00:18:28,211 --> 00:18:32,241
- So, does she start chemo now?
- I wouldn't know about that.

272
00:18:32,581 --> 00:18:34,281
They decide the treatment plan...

273
00:18:34,281 --> 00:18:36,751
after analyzing
the removed tissue...

274
00:18:36,821 --> 00:18:38,851
once the final staging is complete.

275
00:18:39,521 --> 00:18:42,821
Wow, that's so impressive.
You're a total brainiac.

276
00:18:43,261 --> 00:18:47,331
- I know. Book smarts are genetic.
- Totally.

277
00:18:48,531 --> 00:18:51,531
Who do you take after?
What do your parents do?

278
00:18:54,471 --> 00:18:56,771
They sell cars.

279
00:18:57,201 --> 00:18:58,801
- I see.
- What?

280
00:18:59,271 --> 00:19:01,441
Didn't you say before
that both your parents are doctors?

281
00:19:01,811 --> 00:19:04,141
What? No, I didn't.

282
00:19:04,811 --> 00:19:06,111
You must be thinking
of someone else.

283
00:19:06,551 --> 00:19:07,551
Was I?

284
00:19:08,681 --> 00:19:09,821
But where's Dong Ik?

285
00:19:10,251 --> 00:19:11,951
Is he not eating?
Why isn't he out here yet?

286
00:19:12,481 --> 00:19:15,891
Oh, he went out last night
and drank too much.

287
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:20,491
Oh, my.

288
00:19:21,131 --> 00:19:22,131
Honey.

289
00:19:22,591 --> 00:19:25,061
I thought you were still asleep.
What are you doing up?

290
00:19:25,601 --> 00:19:27,301
Yes, I woke up early.

291
00:19:27,701 --> 00:19:31,501
I made some bean sprout soup
for your hangover. Want some?

292
00:19:32,301 --> 00:19:33,611
It's okay. I don't have an appetite.

293
00:19:41,881 --> 00:19:43,521
What on earth are you thinking,
Pacu Nacho?

294
00:19:45,051 --> 00:19:47,751
I told you.
I decided to leave as soon as I can.

295
00:19:47,921 --> 00:19:50,861
I know, but why?
Why would you even consider that?

296
00:19:50,961 --> 00:19:55,061
- Seriously. Just calm down.
- How can you expect me to be calm?

297
00:19:55,731 --> 00:19:58,801
International orders are pouring in,
and business is booming.

298
00:19:58,861 --> 00:20:01,301
That's my point.
My job here is done.

299
00:20:01,301 --> 00:20:03,801
The Fashion Division will be fine
without me now, right?

300
00:20:03,971 --> 00:20:06,641
And Gong Ju Ah is more than capable
of leading the Design Team.

301
00:20:07,471 --> 00:20:09,371
Did Ms. Gong agree to this?

302
00:20:10,611 --> 00:20:12,211
- Yes.
- What?

303
00:20:12,811 --> 00:20:13,851
She agreed to break up?

304
00:20:14,251 --> 00:20:15,851
Yes, she did.

305
00:20:17,021 --> 00:20:18,251
Wait, why?

306
00:20:18,721 --> 00:20:21,521
If you can't go public
because Dr. Han is sick,

307
00:20:22,151 --> 00:20:25,091
why don't you just date in secret
until the treatment is over?

308
00:20:25,961 --> 00:20:27,491
I'm tired of lying to our parents.

309
00:20:27,591 --> 00:20:29,391
But does that mean you have to
move abroad?

310
00:20:29,461 --> 00:20:31,631
- Should I move to another company?
- No way.

311
00:20:32,661 --> 00:20:35,101
You're driving me crazy.
You think this is funny?

312
00:20:36,331 --> 00:20:39,771
- You want me to cry instead?
- Forget it. Just don't break up.

313
00:20:40,341 --> 00:20:41,341
What?

314
00:20:41,411 --> 00:20:46,081
Why only marriage or a breakup?
You could try long-distance.

315
00:20:46,311 --> 00:20:49,451
Gosh, you and Park Jun Hyeok
are exactly alike, you know?

316
00:20:49,511 --> 00:20:51,721
Hey, stop getting so worked up
about it, okay?

317
00:20:52,221 --> 00:20:54,491
I'm only saying this because
I know how deep your love was.

318
00:20:57,961 --> 00:20:59,191
Are you sure you'll be okay?

319
00:21:00,691 --> 00:21:02,991
I don't know. I guess I'll find out.

320
00:21:11,001 --> 00:21:12,001
What is it?

321
00:21:14,311 --> 00:21:16,781
Didn't you break up with Hyun Bin?

322
00:21:17,581 --> 00:21:19,911
- We did.
- Then why are you humming?

323
00:21:20,281 --> 00:21:25,051
I'm happy Mom's surgery went well,
and the launch show was a success.

324
00:21:25,081 --> 00:21:27,191
So I guess I just started humming
without realizing it.

325
00:21:29,091 --> 00:21:30,161
Hey, Gong Woo Jae.

326
00:21:30,621 --> 00:21:33,461
Too bad for you,
I can't grant your wish.

327
00:21:34,331 --> 00:21:36,231
What wish are you talking about?

328
00:21:36,561 --> 00:21:39,031
That I get married quickly
and move out.

329
00:21:39,731 --> 00:21:41,301
Are you really okay, though?

330
00:21:42,731 --> 00:21:45,941
Of course, I am.
We didn't date for that long.

331
00:21:46,601 --> 00:21:50,841
I was so nervous we'd get caught,
so honestly, it's a relief.

332
00:22:00,691 --> 00:22:02,751
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

333
00:22:03,391 --> 00:22:05,021
Mom, are you feeling any better?

334
00:22:06,221 --> 00:22:08,491
Gosh, you kids.

335
00:22:08,731 --> 00:22:11,301
I just saw you yesterday.
Why are you all here again?

336
00:22:11,461 --> 00:22:13,801
I wanted to see you
before I go to work.

337
00:22:14,771 --> 00:22:16,401
Ju Ah, what about work?

338
00:22:16,531 --> 00:22:18,501
I took the morning off,
so I'm going in this afternoon.

339
00:22:19,101 --> 00:22:22,071
By the way,
I have a solo interview coming up.

340
00:22:22,711 --> 00:22:24,711
What? Really?

341
00:22:25,081 --> 00:22:27,281
It's going to be a main feature
in a fashion magazine.

342
00:22:27,781 --> 00:22:28,851
Oh, my goodness.

343
00:22:29,711 --> 00:22:31,621
And you have me to thank for that.

344
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:35,051
She's right.
The model was so amazing,

345
00:22:35,121 --> 00:22:36,691
the clothes you made
shone even brighter.

346
00:22:36,991 --> 00:22:37,991
Agreed.

347
00:22:38,261 --> 00:22:40,891
The outfit you wore
got the best reaction.

348
00:22:41,191 --> 00:22:42,861
- Really?
- Yes!

349
00:22:44,801 --> 00:22:47,301
- What's wrong?
- What is it? Mom, are you in pain?

350
00:22:47,631 --> 00:22:49,971
Gosh, I guess
the painkillers aren't working.

351
00:22:50,271 --> 00:22:53,001
Mom, if you can't stand it,
should we ask for more painkillers?

352
00:22:53,001 --> 00:22:54,041
Yes...

353
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:56,781
Yes, good idea.
Woo Jae, go get the nurse.

354
00:22:56,841 --> 00:22:57,841
Okay.

355
00:23:00,311 --> 00:23:01,381
My gosh...

356
00:23:02,281 --> 00:23:03,821
Just hang in there. It's okay.

357
00:23:07,091 --> 00:23:08,251
What's with all this stuff?

358
00:23:08,751 --> 00:23:10,921
I bought a few things
your sister-in-law might need.

359
00:23:11,461 --> 00:23:13,461
Goodness, all this?

360
00:23:13,791 --> 00:23:17,161
I figured these cushions would help
in a few places, so I got several.

361
00:23:17,401 --> 00:23:20,731
I also got some lightweight cups.
I figured her arm would be too weak.

362
00:23:21,331 --> 00:23:22,371
Dorphini.

363
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:27,371
This is an oil to help her sleep,
and I also got some moisturizer.

364
00:23:27,811 --> 00:23:31,381
I heard that chemo and radiation
can weaken the skin barrier.

365
00:23:32,581 --> 00:23:34,451
You're so incredibly thoughtful.

366
00:23:35,511 --> 00:23:36,511
It's nothing.

367
00:23:37,681 --> 00:23:40,051
Oh, you know we're catching
a late movie after work...

368
00:23:40,051 --> 00:23:41,191
with Jin Ah
and her boyfriend, right?

369
00:23:41,351 --> 00:23:45,361
Let's tell them to go without us.
Seong Mi is sick.

370
00:23:45,561 --> 00:23:48,391
But it's a late show.
We should still go.

371
00:23:49,131 --> 00:23:52,301
- All right. I'm off.
- Okay, be safe.

372
00:23:52,301 --> 00:23:54,131
I'm swamped.
Where on earth did he go?

373
00:23:55,301 --> 00:23:56,331
Hey, Jeong Han.

374
00:23:57,541 --> 00:24:00,141
Hey... Jeong Han. Hi.

375
00:24:02,011 --> 00:24:04,081
- We were just...
- Hello.

376
00:24:04,611 --> 00:24:08,781
- Yes.
- Right, thanks a lot, Dong Suk.

377
00:24:09,111 --> 00:24:10,121
Yes, thank you.

378
00:24:11,521 --> 00:24:12,781
My goodness.

379
00:24:12,781 --> 00:24:14,221
- Hey.
- Yes?

380
00:24:14,451 --> 00:24:17,421
What were you two doing here?
And what's that?

381
00:24:17,491 --> 00:24:20,661
This? Dong Suk bought some things
Seong Mi,

382
00:24:21,161 --> 00:24:24,561
- and she dropped it off.
- Dong Suk did? For my Seong Mi?

383
00:24:25,161 --> 00:24:26,161
Yes.

384
00:24:26,601 --> 00:24:29,871
Yes, she was going to drop them off
at Mom's pharmacy,

385
00:24:29,931 --> 00:24:31,141
but Mom wasn't there,
so she gave them to me.

386
00:24:31,201 --> 00:24:35,211
She could've come to the clinic.
Why meet up separately for this?

387
00:24:38,241 --> 00:24:39,411
Hey, you.

388
00:24:39,981 --> 00:24:41,051
You...

389
00:24:45,221 --> 00:24:48,291
Your girl will get the wrong idea,
man.

390
00:24:49,351 --> 00:24:51,991
What's to get the wrong idea about?
She's just Woo Jae's boss.

391
00:24:52,061 --> 00:24:53,591
What wrong idea?

392
00:24:53,961 --> 00:24:58,461
Don't you know how people will talk?
If you're seen hanging out with her,

393
00:24:58,531 --> 00:25:02,501
they'll say you're like our father
and Dong Ik's mother. You get it?

394
00:25:02,671 --> 00:25:07,611
Remember? Your ex-wife
and her ex had an affair and...

395
00:25:07,671 --> 00:25:09,941
Goodness, I get it, okay? Just stop.

396
00:25:10,011 --> 00:25:12,641
Why do you keep spelling out
every single detail?

397
00:25:12,881 --> 00:25:15,181
And besides,
not everyone even knows that story.

398
00:25:15,251 --> 00:25:17,251
So you should be quiet about it.
Got it?

399
00:25:17,651 --> 00:25:19,581
Hey, anyway, about these...

400
00:25:19,681 --> 00:25:23,121
Don't you dare tell Seong Mi
that Dong Suk gave you this.

401
00:25:23,221 --> 00:25:26,221
What? Dong Suk brought all this
since she was thinking of her. Why?

402
00:25:26,291 --> 00:25:29,331
Listen. Don't you know
most of her stress was caused...

403
00:25:29,391 --> 00:25:33,331
by that awful family?
From now on, I'll cut them off...

404
00:25:33,431 --> 00:25:37,441
at the source so my Seong Mi
never has to deal with them again.

405
00:25:37,501 --> 00:25:38,541
And you'd better act accordingly.

406
00:25:39,201 --> 00:25:40,211
Hey.

407
00:25:41,041 --> 00:25:43,711
Seriously, why are you so on edge?
Is something wrong?

408
00:25:44,411 --> 00:25:46,581
On top of your
sister-in-law's condition,

409
00:25:46,641 --> 00:25:49,281
my patient schedule
is just completely packed, and...

410
00:25:49,451 --> 00:25:52,421
- I feel like I'm losing my mind.
- Oh, man.

411
00:25:52,781 --> 00:25:54,391
Why are you just
telling me this now?

412
00:25:54,851 --> 00:25:56,491
I just need to reschedule
two appointments.

413
00:25:56,551 --> 00:25:59,091
Oh, really? Hey,
can you cover for me then?

414
00:25:59,161 --> 00:26:00,391
Thanks. That would be a huge help.

415
00:26:00,461 --> 00:26:03,031
Don't thank me.
She's my sister-in-law.

416
00:26:03,091 --> 00:26:07,031
Don't be ridiculous. I'll handle
your appointments, so don't worry.

417
00:26:07,231 --> 00:26:08,671
- Yes, okay.
- All right.

418
00:26:08,671 --> 00:26:10,341
- Go on, hurry up.
- Okay.

419
00:26:11,041 --> 00:26:13,001
Hey, Dong Suk got these
for your wife!

420
00:26:13,071 --> 00:26:15,011
I heard you. Just go.
Hurry up. Go on!

421
00:26:22,011 --> 00:26:25,621
Hey, why don't you two go on ahead?
I'm running a little late.

422
00:26:26,081 --> 00:26:28,191
We'll wait. It's still early.

423
00:26:28,291 --> 00:26:30,861
No, it's okay. Go ahead.
I'll be right there.

424
00:26:31,391 --> 00:26:33,591
Okay, take your time.
We'll go on ahead and get set up.

425
00:26:34,361 --> 00:26:35,361
Let's go.

426
00:26:54,151 --> 00:26:55,151
What's this?

427
00:26:55,911 --> 00:26:57,651
She carries her passport around?

428
00:27:01,451 --> 00:27:03,191
- Mom.
- Oh, boy.

429
00:27:03,721 --> 00:27:06,261
What did the surgeon
who operated on Seong Mi say?

430
00:27:06,521 --> 00:27:11,001
They said there was no metastasis
to the lymph nodes and it went well,

431
00:27:11,201 --> 00:27:15,271
but seeing her in so much pain
makes me worry something went wrong.

432
00:27:15,731 --> 00:27:18,001
I know. For her to be
in this much pain...

433
00:27:18,541 --> 00:27:20,541
I don't know if she should really
be discharged tomorrow.

434
00:27:23,311 --> 00:27:28,081
- Dae Han. What brings you here?
- Hi, Seong Mi.

435
00:27:28,351 --> 00:27:31,681
Luckily, I had a cancellation
in my schedule today.

436
00:27:31,751 --> 00:27:33,521
Jeong Han is dying to come see you.

437
00:27:34,391 --> 00:27:37,361
- I just need to...
- Sure. Hold on one second.

438
00:27:38,661 --> 00:27:41,291
Seong Mi, what is it?
Do you need to use the restroom?

439
00:27:41,391 --> 00:27:43,801
Then hop on my back.
I'll take you there.

440
00:27:43,931 --> 00:27:45,061
No, that's okay.

441
00:27:45,961 --> 00:27:50,171
I feel nauseous,
maybe from all the painkillers.

442
00:27:50,231 --> 00:27:52,201
I just wanted to sit up for a bit.

443
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:53,971
You're nauseous? Hold on.

444
00:27:54,541 --> 00:27:55,871
In that case...

445
00:27:56,741 --> 00:27:58,911
I'll give you a foot massage.

446
00:27:58,981 --> 00:28:02,381
No, you don't have to.
That's too embarrassing.

447
00:28:02,481 --> 00:28:06,151
Don't be embarrassed with family.
Besides, I'm a professional.

448
00:28:06,221 --> 00:28:10,051
Right, why be embarrassed?
Let him help you. Here.

449
00:28:10,221 --> 00:28:14,461
- Really. No.
- Wait, careful. Watch your feet.

450
00:28:14,531 --> 00:28:17,861
Seong Mi, just let me try.
It's okay. Here.

451
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:22,201
This spot here
in the middle of your sole...

452
00:28:22,601 --> 00:28:25,271
and your heel...
If I massage these spots,

453
00:28:25,771 --> 00:28:27,471
it should help with the nausea.

454
00:28:29,811 --> 00:28:32,511
I must have saved a country
in my past life...

455
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:35,651
to end up with such a sweet
brother-in-law.

456
00:28:36,011 --> 00:28:37,251
Then,

457
00:28:38,051 --> 00:28:40,951
I must have achieved world peace
in my past life.

458
00:28:41,591 --> 00:28:43,521
To have a sister-in-law
as wonderful as you.

459
00:28:46,961 --> 00:28:48,261
Here, let me.

460
00:28:52,061 --> 00:28:53,771
(Patient Room)

461
00:28:55,801 --> 00:28:56,831
Hey, Dorphini.

462
00:28:57,841 --> 00:28:58,841
Oh, man... What should I do?

463
00:29:00,041 --> 00:29:02,141
I don't think I can make it
to the movies today.

464
00:29:02,411 --> 00:29:05,011
I'm at the hospital
with my sister-in-law right now.

465
00:29:05,511 --> 00:29:06,541
I'm so sorry.

466
00:29:06,941 --> 00:29:10,721
Sorry? Don't be silly.
Of course, we'll meet again.

467
00:29:11,221 --> 00:29:13,251
We can always see the movie
some other time.

468
00:29:13,451 --> 00:29:16,591
I already bought the tickets,
so do you want to go by yourself?

469
00:29:16,951 --> 00:29:19,221
Gosh, no, never mind.
That'd be weird.

470
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:20,591
I'll just cancel them.

471
00:29:20,931 --> 00:29:23,561
Okay. So are you staying
at the hospital tonight?

472
00:29:23,691 --> 00:29:27,331
Yes, I'm going to send Mom home
and stay the night.

473
00:29:28,601 --> 00:29:32,101
My brother's too busy,
so he can't make it.

474
00:29:33,071 --> 00:29:35,341
You'll be so uncomfortable
sleeping at the hospital.

475
00:29:36,771 --> 00:29:38,381
Okay, got it.

476
00:29:41,251 --> 00:29:42,981
Did Uncle go to the hospital?

477
00:29:42,981 --> 00:29:45,721
Yes, he'll send Ms. Na home and...

478
00:29:49,621 --> 00:29:53,661
Woo Jae, wait. How did you know
I was talking to your uncle?

479
00:29:54,761 --> 00:29:56,791
Oh, that's...

480
00:29:58,801 --> 00:30:01,271
You... Do you know something?

481
00:30:01,871 --> 00:30:03,001
Yes.

482
00:30:03,631 --> 00:30:05,071
It was pretty obvious.

483
00:30:07,741 --> 00:30:09,641
I'll just pretend
I don't know anything.

484
00:30:10,911 --> 00:30:14,281
Listen,
since your mom is sick and all,

485
00:30:14,351 --> 00:30:17,951
I'll be careful not to let
the rest of the family find out.

486
00:30:18,781 --> 00:30:20,321
Don't worry about me.

487
00:30:20,651 --> 00:30:24,691
I'm sure my uncle has a plan.
I trust he knows what he's doing.

488
00:30:32,431 --> 00:30:34,401
Wow, look at these scallops.
Scallops!

489
00:30:35,571 --> 00:30:37,171
- Oh, it's hot!
- Stop.

490
00:30:37,171 --> 00:30:38,841
- There, is that okay?
- Yes.

491
00:30:39,201 --> 00:30:40,841
- Thank you. Yes!
- Enjoy your meal.

492
00:30:46,781 --> 00:30:48,011
Yes, Mr. Gong.

493
00:30:50,551 --> 00:30:52,081
You two can't make it to the movie?

494
00:30:53,621 --> 00:30:55,151
Then we'll just cancel ours too.

495
00:30:55,721 --> 00:30:57,921
Right. Yes, I understand. Okay.

496
00:31:00,491 --> 00:31:03,261
Wait.
What do you think you're doing?

497
00:31:03,791 --> 00:31:06,531
- What?
- Why would you cancel our tickets?

498
00:31:07,161 --> 00:31:10,071
Because we were all supposed to go,
but they can't make it.

499
00:31:11,301 --> 00:31:13,701
Is the thought of seeing a movie
alone with me that horrible?

500
00:31:13,801 --> 00:31:17,581
No, of course not.
But a plan is a plan.

501
00:31:22,051 --> 00:31:25,851
You're so clueless and by-the-book.
Unbelievable.

502
00:31:27,491 --> 00:31:30,761
- Are you mad?
- No. I'm not mad.

503
00:31:31,621 --> 00:31:32,861
That's a relief.

504
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:35,291
I was so nervous for a second there.
I thought you were mad at me.

505
00:31:35,561 --> 00:31:38,661
Jin Ah, try this kimchi. Here.

506
00:31:38,731 --> 00:31:41,071
The owner makes it from scratch.
It's really delicious.

507
00:32:03,621 --> 00:32:04,791
Hey, you're here.

508
00:32:05,391 --> 00:32:07,261
Yes, to get your signature.

509
00:32:07,961 --> 00:32:09,191
So, where are you off to?

510
00:32:10,391 --> 00:32:13,401
Oh, this...
These are the handover documents.

511
00:32:13,971 --> 00:32:14,971
Already?

512
00:32:15,371 --> 00:32:18,901
Wow, once you make up your mind,
you don't waste any time.

513
00:32:19,241 --> 00:32:21,571
I told the Vice President
I'm quitting, too.

514
00:32:22,571 --> 00:32:25,881
- She must have flipped.
- Gosh, don't even get me started.

515
00:32:26,281 --> 00:32:28,181
It took everything I had
to calm her down.

516
00:32:28,681 --> 00:32:31,851
I also told my parents
and put my apartment on the market.

517
00:32:32,851 --> 00:32:35,051
Wow. That stings a little.

518
00:32:36,051 --> 00:32:37,691
You're getting everything done
so fast,

519
00:32:37,691 --> 00:32:38,991
like you've been waiting to leave.

520
00:32:41,191 --> 00:32:43,761
Isn't your family upset about it?

521
00:32:44,161 --> 00:32:47,061
I'll have to spend time with them
before I leave.

522
00:32:50,171 --> 00:32:51,841
Is there anything I can do to help?

523
00:32:52,541 --> 00:32:53,541
No, I'm good.

524
00:32:53,841 --> 00:32:56,571
I have a marketing meeting.
I'll be back.

525
00:32:56,641 --> 00:32:58,281
Just leave the file here.

526
00:32:58,881 --> 00:32:59,881
Okay.

527
00:33:01,781 --> 00:33:02,811
Hey...

528
00:33:08,151 --> 00:33:09,151
About us...

529
00:33:09,851 --> 00:33:11,461
For the time we have left,

530
00:33:11,791 --> 00:33:14,361
let's just smile
and get along like this.

531
00:33:17,131 --> 00:33:18,131
Okay.

532
00:33:27,571 --> 00:33:28,671
Dong Ik, you brat.

533
00:33:29,041 --> 00:33:30,811
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

534
00:33:33,341 --> 00:33:35,281
(Hair Salon)

535
00:33:38,151 --> 00:33:41,321
You look better in person
than on TV.

536
00:33:41,791 --> 00:33:42,921
You remember me?

537
00:33:43,451 --> 00:33:46,521
Of course.
I saw you at the beauty pageant.

538
00:33:46,991 --> 00:33:50,091
You were so smitten with Jeong Sun,
you just stood there, jaw dropped.

539
00:33:51,801 --> 00:33:55,671
Please don't tell my wife
I was here.

540
00:33:55,871 --> 00:34:00,641
I don't have her number.
She cut me off to hide her past.

541
00:34:02,071 --> 00:34:06,741
If I hadn't seen you on TV,
I'd have never recognized Jeong Sun.

542
00:34:07,081 --> 00:34:09,711
She looked so classy and well-off.

543
00:34:11,121 --> 00:34:13,351
Anyway, it's been a while.

544
00:34:18,721 --> 00:34:20,931
Well, I was wondering...

545
00:34:21,161 --> 00:34:23,931
She had a daughter.
You're here to ask about her, right?

546
00:34:24,901 --> 00:34:26,201
Well...

547
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:29,771
I was tricked by a private detective
and already spilled the beans.

548
00:34:29,831 --> 00:34:33,301
I might as well get it off my chest.
Ask whatever you're curious about.

549
00:34:35,511 --> 00:34:36,641
If she had a child,

550
00:34:37,811 --> 00:34:39,241
how could she compete
in a beauty pageant?

551
00:34:39,881 --> 00:34:40,881
The child...

552
00:34:41,181 --> 00:34:42,651
Her birth was never
officially registered.

553
00:34:43,551 --> 00:34:45,321
So on paper, she was still single.

554
00:34:45,681 --> 00:34:48,751
I told her to enter the pageant and
meet a rich man to change her life.

555
00:34:48,791 --> 00:34:50,091
I'm the one who pushed her to do it.

556
00:34:50,791 --> 00:34:53,991
She met you and got her lucky break,
all thanks to me.

557
00:34:57,291 --> 00:34:58,361
Why was the child...

558
00:34:59,461 --> 00:35:00,661
put up for adoption?

559
00:35:00,971 --> 00:35:05,001
She was young,
and after losing the father,

560
00:35:05,271 --> 00:35:06,541
raising a child alone
couldn't have been easy.

561
00:35:07,001 --> 00:35:08,171
Still, she worked with the baby...

562
00:35:08,171 --> 00:35:09,841
on her back
until the child's first birthday.

563
00:35:10,371 --> 00:35:13,941
Then out of nowhere,
a good couple offered to adopt.

564
00:35:14,211 --> 00:35:15,711
She was torn.

565
00:35:15,711 --> 00:35:18,451
But that's still better than
growing up in the back of a salon.

566
00:35:18,621 --> 00:35:19,621
Don't you think?

567
00:35:21,051 --> 00:35:22,351
But still, Jeong Sun...

568
00:35:22,621 --> 00:35:25,291
She saved every penny she could
for that kid.

569
00:35:25,791 --> 00:35:28,531
She wanted to save up a large sum
so she could someday...

570
00:35:28,531 --> 00:35:30,361
be a real mother to her daughter.

571
00:35:30,931 --> 00:35:34,001
She's still saving for that dream,
isn't she?

572
00:35:35,001 --> 00:35:37,301
My goodness,
the child must have grown up by now.

573
00:35:52,381 --> 00:35:54,191
Hasn't Dad been acting
a little weird lately?

574
00:35:54,991 --> 00:35:58,791
Yes. He seems really down.
And he's barely saying a word.

575
00:35:58,891 --> 00:36:00,161
(3H Acupressure Bed)

576
00:36:00,261 --> 00:36:03,231
I think Mom's been so busy
with the new store...

577
00:36:03,291 --> 00:36:05,801
that she hasn't been paying
much attention to Dad,

578
00:36:05,801 --> 00:36:07,401
so he probably feels neglected.
Right?

579
00:36:09,701 --> 00:36:12,241
Yes. I think you're right.

580
00:36:13,041 --> 00:36:17,011
Plus, the show didn't do that well,
and our video got a lot of hate.

581
00:36:17,271 --> 00:36:18,781
He has every reason to be upset.

582
00:36:20,381 --> 00:36:23,211
Hey, should we try to come up
with an idea to help cheer him up?

583
00:36:23,811 --> 00:36:24,821
What kind of idea?

584
00:36:24,921 --> 00:36:26,221
(Sister)

585
00:36:26,321 --> 00:36:29,121
- Well...
- How about...

586
00:36:29,921 --> 00:36:31,761
- A party?
- Yes.

587
00:36:33,591 --> 00:36:35,761
I'm not sure.

588
00:36:37,031 --> 00:36:38,031
I could throw a surprise party...

589
00:36:44,441 --> 00:36:45,471
Sister.

590
00:36:46,941 --> 00:36:49,111
I was worried because
I couldn't reach you.

591
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:52,681
I'm unreachable
when I'm on a retreat.

592
00:36:53,081 --> 00:36:55,011
But Stella, is something the matter?

593
00:36:55,211 --> 00:36:56,451
Well...

594
00:36:57,781 --> 00:36:58,781
By any chance...

595
00:37:01,991 --> 00:37:03,151
Veronica...

596
00:37:05,521 --> 00:37:06,791
Did she come to Korea?

597
00:37:08,661 --> 00:37:12,201
- It's just that...
- Please tell me.

598
00:37:13,801 --> 00:37:14,871
Did Veronica...

599
00:37:16,301 --> 00:37:17,841
Did she come looking for you,
Sister?

600
00:37:19,541 --> 00:37:21,571
So did you tell her where I live?

601
00:37:22,071 --> 00:37:25,841
No, Stella.
Since you didn't want to see her,

602
00:37:26,111 --> 00:37:28,711
I sent her away without
giving her your contact info.

603
00:37:34,391 --> 00:37:35,591
So she really did come.

604
00:37:36,551 --> 00:37:39,791
Did Veronica come to see you? How?

605
00:37:40,791 --> 00:37:41,791
I don't know.

606
00:37:44,301 --> 00:37:46,201
I don't know what's going on.

607
00:37:48,801 --> 00:37:51,071
I don't even know
if it's really Veronica.

608
00:37:51,971 --> 00:37:55,871
All I know is that
she came with a friend her age.

609
00:37:58,811 --> 00:38:00,541
(Deep-Tissue Acupressure and Massage
for Spinal Muscles)

610
00:38:07,351 --> 00:38:08,351
A friend?

611
00:38:09,391 --> 00:38:12,791
Are you looking for that box
that was wrapped in a cloth?

612
00:38:14,461 --> 00:38:15,461
Yes.

613
00:38:15,931 --> 00:38:18,801
I threw it out.
It didn't seem important.

614
00:38:21,731 --> 00:38:22,731
Did you open it?

615
00:38:23,001 --> 00:38:24,571
No.
You said it was just soap, right?

616
00:39:10,711 --> 00:39:11,721
Hey, Eun Bin.

617
00:39:13,151 --> 00:39:15,121
Listen,
something urgent just came up.

618
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:19,161
I'm sorry to ask,

619
00:39:19,761 --> 00:39:21,661
but could you and Min Seo
close up the shop tonight?

620
00:39:23,961 --> 00:39:25,061
Sure.

621
00:39:25,761 --> 00:39:27,501
And grab my bag for me.

622
00:39:29,031 --> 00:39:30,301
Okay, thanks.

623
00:41:21,581 --> 00:41:22,611
What do I do?

624
00:41:24,111 --> 00:41:28,221
What am I going to do? What do I do?

625
00:41:33,621 --> 00:41:35,031
What do I do...

626
00:41:40,361 --> 00:41:44,871
- I'm home.
- Honey, did you eat dinner yet?

627
00:41:45,071 --> 00:41:48,071
No, I came home to eat with you,
Grandma.

628
00:41:48,641 --> 00:41:50,611
Good. Come on in and eat.

629
00:41:50,841 --> 00:41:53,441
- Eat first, then wash up, okay?
- Wow, I really lucked out.

630
00:41:59,751 --> 00:42:00,881
Did you get some rest, Grandma?

631
00:42:01,191 --> 00:42:02,551
How's Mom's nausea?
Is she feeling any better?

632
00:42:02,651 --> 00:42:06,661
Your uncle gave her a foot massage,
and she said she feels much better.

633
00:42:06,721 --> 00:42:11,601
- He's one of a kind, isn't he?
- Tell me about it. Not her husband.

634
00:42:11,901 --> 00:42:15,631
Come on. Dad's been
really good to her lately.

635
00:42:15,831 --> 00:42:17,871
He should've been like that
all along.

636
00:42:18,471 --> 00:42:20,371
Don't say that.
It makes me feel guilty.

637
00:42:22,311 --> 00:42:23,311
Ju Ah.

638
00:42:24,111 --> 00:42:28,511
I'm so glad I came home.
Nothing beats your cooking, Grandma.

639
00:42:30,181 --> 00:42:32,121
All these side dishes are so good,
Grandma.

640
00:42:41,461 --> 00:42:43,631
Father, what are you staring at?

641
00:42:44,261 --> 00:42:47,431
It's just...
That part-timer looks familiar.

642
00:42:48,271 --> 00:42:50,301
- Me?
- She's my daughter's friend.

643
00:42:50,501 --> 00:42:54,401
Oh, my! But it's amazing
how much you two look alike.

644
00:42:54,711 --> 00:42:55,971
So you had your daughter back then.

645
00:42:56,311 --> 00:42:58,641
Hey, she looks just like you.

646
00:43:08,451 --> 00:43:09,691
Honey, you're late.

647
00:43:10,691 --> 00:43:11,921
I'm going to wash up
and get some rest.

648
00:43:22,271 --> 00:43:24,331
(Cha Se Ri, Bankbook, Nuri Bank)

649
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:35,951
(Commercial Property
Sales Agreement)

650
00:43:40,151 --> 00:43:42,591
She wanted to save up a large sum
so she could someday...

651
00:43:42,591 --> 00:43:44,451
be a real mother to her daughter.

652
00:43:44,661 --> 00:43:47,691
She's still saving for that dream,
isn't she?

653
00:43:48,491 --> 00:43:49,661
The child must have grown up by now.

654
00:44:02,241 --> 00:44:05,411
"As he told a story,
she wasn't really listening."

655
00:44:06,041 --> 00:44:09,111
She wasn't really listening
as he was telling a story.

656
00:44:10,581 --> 00:44:13,351
Min Seo, what's the difference
between "as" and "when?"

657
00:44:13,621 --> 00:44:16,791
Min Ji Hu, how do you not know that?
Seriously?

658
00:44:16,921 --> 00:44:18,661
Do you know? You don't know either.

659
00:44:18,961 --> 00:44:21,661
You're right. Min Seo,
can you explain it to me, too?

660
00:44:22,191 --> 00:44:23,331
Okay, Eun Bin.

661
00:44:24,191 --> 00:44:27,061
When Min Seo leaves,
you'll miss her more than I will.

662
00:44:27,261 --> 00:44:31,231
Tell me about it. My sister.

663
00:44:31,701 --> 00:44:33,941
I'll just have to go to Baltimore
then.

664
00:44:34,841 --> 00:44:35,941
Even though you don't speak
any English.

665
00:44:36,041 --> 00:44:38,181
Hey. Be quiet, please.

666
00:44:38,181 --> 00:44:39,411
Hey, I'm going to see
my little sister.

667
00:44:39,411 --> 00:44:41,611
So what if my English isn't perfect?
Right, Min Seo?

668
00:44:44,451 --> 00:44:46,051
So, what was it about "as?"

669
00:46:28,321 --> 00:46:29,321
Hey.

670
00:46:30,721 --> 00:46:31,861
Keep it down.

671
00:46:33,021 --> 00:46:35,491
Hey, how is she?

672
00:46:36,191 --> 00:46:39,261
She's full of painkillers
and just fell asleep.

673
00:46:39,501 --> 00:46:41,631
That's a relief.

674
00:46:42,371 --> 00:46:45,641
Hey, I'll stay the night.
You should go home.

675
00:46:46,141 --> 00:46:48,441
No, it's fine.
Go home and get some sleep.

676
00:46:48,541 --> 00:46:51,241
No, forget it, man. I'll stay here.

677
00:46:51,441 --> 00:46:54,241
I'll sleep here tonight
and check her out tomorrow.

678
00:46:54,611 --> 00:46:55,611
I want to stay too.

679
00:46:56,711 --> 00:46:57,811
I'm too worried to leave.

680
00:47:00,621 --> 00:47:01,791
All right, then.

681
00:47:02,191 --> 00:47:04,151
- Hey, sit down.
- Okay.

682
00:47:04,591 --> 00:47:05,591
Quiet.

683
00:47:11,431 --> 00:47:14,531
(Strict Bed Rest)

684
00:47:19,001 --> 00:47:21,771
- Yes?
- Eun Bin, are you asleep?

685
00:47:22,311 --> 00:47:23,311
No.

686
00:47:25,381 --> 00:47:27,381
Mom, why aren't you asleep?
It's so late.

687
00:47:33,251 --> 00:47:34,321
What?

688
00:47:35,691 --> 00:47:37,491
Why? What's going on?

689
00:47:40,391 --> 00:47:42,191
- Eun Bin.
- Yes?

690
00:47:44,091 --> 00:47:45,331
Did you know?

691
00:47:46,701 --> 00:47:47,701
Know what?

692
00:47:49,871 --> 00:47:50,871
About Min Seo.

693
00:47:53,341 --> 00:47:54,341
Veronica.

694
00:47:57,771 --> 00:47:59,341
What on earth is going on?

695
00:48:00,681 --> 00:48:02,611
Why in the world is she here?

696
00:48:02,611 --> 00:48:04,811
Don't tell me you knew everything
and brought her here, did you?

697
00:48:04,811 --> 00:48:05,981
Mom, calm down.

698
00:48:06,581 --> 00:48:09,321
It was fate
that brought Min Seo here.

699
00:48:10,621 --> 00:48:11,621
What did you just say?

700
00:48:11,991 --> 00:48:14,721
I was suspicious at first, too,
but it's not what you think.

701
00:48:15,561 --> 00:48:17,191
That's not who Min Seo is, Mom.

702
00:48:19,601 --> 00:48:20,601
So then,

703
00:48:22,571 --> 00:48:23,571
she knows...

704
00:48:26,371 --> 00:48:27,571
that I'm her mother?

705
00:48:30,611 --> 00:48:31,611
She knows, doesn't she?

706
00:48:34,951 --> 00:48:35,951
You...

707
00:48:37,051 --> 00:48:38,951
Did you go with her
to see the Sister, too?

708
00:48:40,181 --> 00:48:41,251
Yes.

709
00:48:42,821 --> 00:48:44,451
What were you even thinking?

710
00:48:45,191 --> 00:48:47,861
How could you lie to your mother?

711
00:48:50,191 --> 00:48:52,001
You said you didn't want to see her.

712
00:48:53,261 --> 00:48:55,971
That our family
was more important to you.

713
00:49:02,941 --> 00:49:03,941
Min Seo...

714
00:49:07,241 --> 00:49:09,081
So she must have heard that.

715
00:49:18,621 --> 00:49:21,931
How much...
She must have hated me so much.

716
00:49:24,131 --> 00:49:26,931
She doesn't blame you, Mom.
She understands.

717
00:49:27,061 --> 00:49:30,071
She understands everything,
and she still wants to be with you.

718
00:49:30,531 --> 00:49:32,701
She said
she just wants to hold your hand...

719
00:49:33,971 --> 00:49:37,111
and help you out, okay?

720
00:49:45,781 --> 00:49:46,781
And you?

721
00:49:50,021 --> 00:49:51,351
Weren't you mad at me?

722
00:49:54,561 --> 00:49:56,491
I'm the one
who abandoned my own child.

723
00:49:58,731 --> 00:50:00,461
But you had no other choice.

724
00:50:01,731 --> 00:50:04,001
Besides, you were even younger
than I am now.

725
00:50:08,371 --> 00:50:09,371
I...

726
00:50:12,681 --> 00:50:14,811
I just knew
I shouldn't be the one to raise her.

727
00:50:16,951 --> 00:50:18,481
In a better home...

728
00:50:20,181 --> 00:50:21,581
where she'd get lots of love...

729
00:50:22,091 --> 00:50:23,591
That's how I wanted her to grow up.

730
00:50:26,621 --> 00:50:27,621
Min Seo...

731
00:50:28,091 --> 00:50:30,291
She said she was showered
with love growing up.

732
00:50:30,361 --> 00:50:33,701
And she's a med student
at Johns Hopkins.

733
00:50:34,201 --> 00:50:36,831
She must have gotten her brains
from you, you know?

734
00:50:41,171 --> 00:50:43,211
- Eun Bin.
- Mom.

735
00:50:45,481 --> 00:50:47,241
You're not going to abandon me,
are you?

736
00:50:47,811 --> 00:50:49,611
What are you talking about?

737
00:50:50,551 --> 00:50:51,651
At first,

738
00:50:54,281 --> 00:50:57,421
I was so scared
I was going to lose you to Min Seo.

739
00:50:59,321 --> 00:51:00,661
But when you told the Sister...

740
00:51:02,731 --> 00:51:04,391
that our family...

741
00:51:05,061 --> 00:51:07,831
meant so much to you,
I was so thankful.

742
00:51:12,941 --> 00:51:13,941
Eun Bin.

743
00:51:14,741 --> 00:51:16,211
I meant every word.

744
00:51:18,271 --> 00:51:19,281
I'm sorry.

745
00:51:20,411 --> 00:51:22,981
My Eun Bin, I'm so sorry.

746
00:51:23,981 --> 00:51:25,621
I'm sorry for putting you
through this.

747
00:51:32,921 --> 00:51:34,661
Don't cry. I'm so sorry.

748
00:51:45,171 --> 00:51:46,541
You should go now.

749
00:51:48,641 --> 00:51:49,711
Min Seo's asleep.

750
00:51:50,271 --> 00:51:53,141
Once she's out,
she's dead to the world.

751
00:52:21,441 --> 00:52:24,211
I must remind you of your mom.

752
00:52:24,611 --> 00:52:27,841
You're still such a kid.
Sweetie, don't cry. Come here.

753
00:52:28,311 --> 00:52:30,811
Come on, what's wrong? It's okay.

754
00:52:32,051 --> 00:52:33,221
Don't cry.

755
00:53:18,861 --> 00:53:19,861
Honey.

756
00:53:21,661 --> 00:53:23,701
You're still up?

757
00:53:27,401 --> 00:53:29,341
- Honey.
- We...

758
00:53:31,441 --> 00:53:32,911
need to talk.

759
00:53:34,341 --> 00:53:35,451
It's late.

760
00:53:35,951 --> 00:53:37,081
Can we talk tomorrow?

761
00:53:38,181 --> 00:53:41,121
I have something to tell you, too.

762
00:53:43,491 --> 00:53:44,491
Really?

763
00:54:03,171 --> 00:54:05,681
Se Ri, before you head to work,

764
00:54:06,011 --> 00:54:08,981
grab your ID and your personal seal.

765
00:54:09,611 --> 00:54:10,611
Pardon me?

766
00:54:10,911 --> 00:54:14,481
A small shop behind the market
just became available.

767
00:54:15,321 --> 00:54:17,351
You're buying another building
in Mom's name?

768
00:54:18,051 --> 00:54:19,761
Father, please, you don't have to.

769
00:54:19,991 --> 00:54:22,431
Dong Ik, stop by tonight...

770
00:54:23,191 --> 00:54:25,331
and sign the contract
in Se Ri's name.

771
00:54:25,961 --> 00:54:26,961
Okay.

772
00:54:26,961 --> 00:54:30,871
You just bought her a shop,
and now you're buying her another.

773
00:54:31,301 --> 00:54:33,301
This one is...

774
00:54:33,901 --> 00:54:36,271
a gift to celebrate her officially
becoming part of the family.

775
00:54:36,371 --> 00:54:38,371
Wow, look at how generous Dad is.

776
00:54:39,041 --> 00:54:40,641
I'm so incredibly jealous of you.

777
00:54:41,911 --> 00:54:44,051
Father, really, I'm fine.

778
00:54:44,581 --> 00:54:46,081
You don't have to do this for me.

779
00:54:49,091 --> 00:54:50,751
- Okay, get home safe.
- Bye now.

780
00:54:50,821 --> 00:54:52,521
- All right, stay healthy.
- Okay. And take care.

781
00:54:53,191 --> 00:54:54,521
(Reception and Payment)

782
00:54:54,591 --> 00:54:56,131
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

783
00:54:57,931 --> 00:54:59,031
What should we get for lunch?

784
00:54:59,531 --> 00:55:02,931
Why did you sleep at the hospital?
Dr. Gong was there, too.

785
00:55:03,131 --> 00:55:07,171
What? Of course, I had to.
I can't be there for her discharge,

786
00:55:07,241 --> 00:55:08,341
and I feel awful about that.

787
00:55:08,371 --> 00:55:12,241
I know how much you care about her,
but...

788
00:55:12,311 --> 00:55:16,151
think about your girlfriend,
not just your sister-in-law.

789
00:55:16,581 --> 00:55:18,111
Canceling a date on the day of
is just...

790
00:55:18,511 --> 00:55:19,781
Isn't that such a rude thing to do?

791
00:55:20,621 --> 00:55:24,951
My Dorphini? She has a big heart.
She completely understands.

792
00:55:25,661 --> 00:55:26,821
Understand, my foot.

793
00:55:27,021 --> 00:55:30,931
She's just not saying she's upset
because she's afraid to sound petty.

794
00:55:30,991 --> 00:55:34,761
Wait a second. Nurse Oh.

795
00:55:36,131 --> 00:55:37,671
Hey, you're pouting about this,
aren't you?

796
00:55:37,931 --> 00:55:39,641
You're upset you couldn't see
the movie yesterday.

797
00:55:39,641 --> 00:55:40,971
No, I'm not.

798
00:55:41,071 --> 00:55:43,171
- What do you mean, no?
- I'm not.

799
00:55:43,471 --> 00:55:44,771
- Good day.
- Good day.

800
00:55:45,611 --> 00:55:48,011
- Mind if I borrow Jin Ah for a bit?
- Not at all.

801
00:55:48,011 --> 00:55:50,511
- We're going to get lunch.
- Right. Go ahead.

802
00:55:50,811 --> 00:55:52,421
- Go on, she's all yours.
- Okay.

803
00:55:52,621 --> 00:55:54,251
Actually, I'm too busy today.

804
00:55:55,251 --> 00:55:56,491
- Really?
- Busy, my foot.

805
00:55:56,491 --> 00:55:58,091
Well, if you're busy, you're busy.

806
00:55:58,351 --> 00:55:59,421
Tomorrow, then.

807
00:56:00,891 --> 00:56:03,491
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

808
00:56:03,561 --> 00:56:05,131
What was that reaction?

809
00:56:06,431 --> 00:56:08,161
See? He's always like that.

810
00:56:09,701 --> 00:56:12,071
He's so dense,
it's driving me crazy.

811
00:56:13,171 --> 00:56:14,271
Excuse me!

812
00:56:15,541 --> 00:56:17,771
Come on, Jin Ah isn't sulking.

813
00:56:17,911 --> 00:56:19,641
If she were sulking,
she would've said so.

814
00:56:19,781 --> 00:56:21,281
What? Seriously?

815
00:56:21,281 --> 00:56:23,881
- Is this your first relationship?
- Yes.

816
00:56:25,481 --> 00:56:29,351
Wow. I don't even know
where to begin with you.

817
00:56:29,451 --> 00:56:31,851
- So I asked her if she was mad.
- And?

818
00:56:31,851 --> 00:56:33,591
Jin Ah said she wasn't.

819
00:56:34,991 --> 00:56:36,661
And you just took her word for it?

820
00:56:36,761 --> 00:56:38,761
Of course. You should trust
the person you like.

821
00:56:39,131 --> 00:56:43,331
Man, and I thought I was dense.
You're on a whole other level.

822
00:56:43,571 --> 00:56:45,301
- Have you two hugged?
- No.

823
00:56:45,301 --> 00:56:46,301
- A peck?
- No.

824
00:56:46,301 --> 00:56:47,441
- Made out?
- No.

825
00:56:48,101 --> 00:56:50,271
You're hopeless!

826
00:56:52,311 --> 00:56:53,311
Careful.

827
00:56:56,551 --> 00:56:59,781
Hey, the place looks a lot cleaner.

828
00:57:02,121 --> 00:57:04,591
I knew all the dust inside
wouldn't be good for you,

829
00:57:04,851 --> 00:57:06,961
so I just got rid of
all the old things.

830
00:57:07,261 --> 00:57:10,161
And the cups and plates
you use all the time.

831
00:57:10,331 --> 00:57:12,531
I moved them to a lower shelf
so they're easier for you to reach.

832
00:57:13,531 --> 00:57:15,631
You shouldn't have gone
to all this trouble for me.

833
00:57:15,901 --> 00:57:18,531
It was no trouble at all.
Of course, I'd do it.

834
00:57:19,041 --> 00:57:22,241
So, are you hungry?
Want me to get you something to eat?

835
00:57:22,911 --> 00:57:26,911
No, thanks. My mouth tastes bad,
so I don't think I can eat.

836
00:57:27,641 --> 00:57:30,611
All right. Let's get you to bed.
Come on.

837
00:57:31,811 --> 00:57:33,221
Watch your other arm.

838
00:57:33,881 --> 00:57:35,021
Careful.

839
00:57:35,521 --> 00:57:36,521
There you go.

840
00:57:39,091 --> 00:57:40,561
What's wrong? Does it hurt again?

841
00:57:41,061 --> 00:57:42,061
Yes.

842
00:57:43,061 --> 00:57:46,361
My chest is throbbing,
and it feels like it's on fire.

843
00:57:47,631 --> 00:57:48,661
What do I do?

844
00:57:50,931 --> 00:57:54,671
I guess you have to be a patient
to understand what it's like.

845
00:57:56,341 --> 00:58:00,011
Hold on. I'll go get
an ice pack, okay?

846
00:58:00,081 --> 00:58:03,381
Just bring me that
and then head out.

847
00:58:03,651 --> 00:58:05,381
Don't you have
your afternoon appointments?

848
00:58:06,721 --> 00:58:08,281
I still have time.

849
00:58:09,191 --> 00:58:11,951
And there's an emergency button
here by your pillow.

850
00:58:12,261 --> 00:58:14,621
If you need anything at all,
just press it. Don't hesitate.

851
00:58:14,891 --> 00:58:18,031
It'll alert my phone,
and I'll come running, okay?

852
00:58:19,201 --> 00:58:20,661
You've really gone all out.

853
00:58:23,771 --> 00:58:25,201
I'm going to try and sleep.

854
00:58:25,701 --> 00:58:27,571
Okay, get some rest.

855
00:58:28,141 --> 00:58:32,311
Watch this arm. There we go. There.

856
00:58:44,491 --> 00:58:45,491
Dad.

857
00:58:46,921 --> 00:58:49,461
- About that building.
- What about it?

858
00:58:50,791 --> 00:58:52,861
Se Ri already has a lot in her name.

859
00:58:53,631 --> 00:58:54,961
I was wondering if we really
have to give her more.

860
00:58:55,531 --> 00:58:57,031
Don't be so cheap.

861
00:58:58,101 --> 00:58:59,271
But, Dad...

862
00:59:00,141 --> 00:59:01,741
The realtor? Why are they calling?

863
00:59:04,271 --> 00:59:05,511
This is Yang Seon Chul.

864
00:59:07,811 --> 00:59:08,981
I see.

865
00:59:10,211 --> 00:59:11,681
Got it.

866
00:59:13,551 --> 00:59:14,551
What is it?

867
00:59:18,751 --> 00:59:19,961
Just grab a quick bite.

868
00:59:20,521 --> 00:59:23,661
Then take Se Ri
to the real estate office.

869
00:59:24,431 --> 00:59:27,901
He's busy with a deal tonight,
so he said to come now.

870
00:59:28,971 --> 00:59:30,201
After you sign the papers,

871
00:59:30,771 --> 00:59:32,471
treat her to a nice lunch.

872
00:59:33,371 --> 00:59:34,371
Okay.

873
00:59:44,281 --> 00:59:46,021
- You're back?
- Yes, Mom.

874
00:59:47,421 --> 00:59:48,421
Go on in.

875
00:59:48,821 --> 00:59:49,821
What's wrong?

876
00:59:55,491 --> 00:59:57,691
How's Seong Mi doing?

877
00:59:58,031 --> 00:59:59,201
She's sleeping right now.

878
00:59:59,801 --> 01:00:01,801
But it seems like the incision site
is bothering her.

879
01:00:02,301 --> 01:00:04,971
Hopefully, she'll feel better
after she gets some rest.

880
01:00:06,671 --> 01:00:08,171
You've changed a lot, son.

881
01:00:08,471 --> 01:00:09,471
What?

882
01:00:09,611 --> 01:00:13,641
You'd upset Seong Mi over your work,
even when she was pregnant.

883
01:00:15,081 --> 01:00:16,951
Do you have to bring that up, Mom?

884
01:00:18,551 --> 01:00:21,251
Anyway, we should get Seong Mi
something to eat.

885
01:00:22,391 --> 01:00:24,721
Should I ask Dae Han
to get something on his way?

886
01:00:24,791 --> 01:00:26,121
No, it's fine.

887
01:00:26,591 --> 01:00:30,661
He's been busy helping Seong Mi.
Just let him have his date.

888
01:00:31,631 --> 01:00:34,101
Seong Mi just got out of
the hospital, and he's on a date?

889
01:00:35,361 --> 01:00:38,131
You stay here. I'll go
buy something Seong Mi likes.

890
01:00:38,201 --> 01:00:39,601
- Okay.
- All right.

891
01:00:47,811 --> 01:00:49,681
- Hi, how are you?
- Hello.

892
01:00:49,751 --> 01:00:53,481
Yes, can I get some dumplings?
A mix of different kinds.

893
01:00:53,721 --> 01:00:55,921
- Just give me a good variety.
- You got it.

894
01:00:57,851 --> 01:01:00,821
Gosh, I hope
she'll at least eat some of these.

895
01:01:02,591 --> 01:01:03,591
This is so good.

896
01:01:03,831 --> 01:01:06,361
- Isn't it so tasty?
- What? What the...

897
01:01:06,431 --> 01:01:07,631
Try the tteokbokki, too. Here.

898
01:01:07,761 --> 01:01:10,901
Is that punk really on a date?
Who is that?

899
01:01:10,971 --> 01:01:14,401
- Okay, let me see her face.
- Like this.

900
01:01:15,871 --> 01:01:16,871
So pretty.

901
01:01:19,641 --> 01:01:21,741
- We're out of pickled radish.
- I'll get more.

902
01:01:21,811 --> 01:01:23,451
No, let me. I'll get it.
You stay here.

903
01:01:23,511 --> 01:01:25,211
- I can get it.
- No, I've got it.

904
01:01:29,421 --> 01:01:30,421
Jeong Han...

905
01:01:34,061 --> 01:01:35,731
(3H Acupressure Bed)

906
01:01:39,961 --> 01:01:43,001
Sweetie. I'm so nervous.

907
01:01:44,131 --> 01:01:47,101
Min Seo's waiting with no idea.
When she finds out you know,

908
01:01:47,171 --> 01:01:48,641
she's going to be so happy,
don't you think?

909
01:01:50,441 --> 01:01:51,441
My sweet daughter...

910
01:01:52,581 --> 01:01:54,441
How did I get
such a kind and beautiful girl?

911
01:01:55,341 --> 01:01:57,611
What are you talking about?
All I ever did was act bratty.

912
01:01:57,881 --> 01:01:58,981
That's not true.

913
01:01:59,681 --> 01:02:01,481
Inside my Eun Bin's heart,

914
01:02:02,181 --> 01:02:04,491
I know
there's a kind and loving girl.

915
01:02:04,751 --> 01:02:06,161
I've always known that.

916
01:02:09,021 --> 01:02:10,031
But, Mom...

917
01:02:10,531 --> 01:02:12,331
Are you really going to tell Dad?

918
01:02:14,661 --> 01:02:15,871
I have to.

919
01:02:16,901 --> 01:02:20,271
I'm meeting him for dinner later,
so I'll explain it all carefully.

920
01:02:20,371 --> 01:02:23,741
Should I come with you?
I can explain it.

921
01:02:23,811 --> 01:02:25,941
No. I'll be the one to talk to him.

922
01:02:26,481 --> 01:02:29,811
Your dad trusts me,
so he'll hear me out.

923
01:02:30,081 --> 01:02:31,211
Don't worry.

924
01:02:32,781 --> 01:02:34,621
You should go.
Min Seo must be waiting.

925
01:02:36,551 --> 01:02:37,591
You can do this!

926
01:02:43,361 --> 01:02:44,361
Go on.

927
01:03:01,581 --> 01:03:04,011
Oh, Mother.

928
01:03:06,881 --> 01:03:10,091
Why are you alone? Eun Bin said
she was treating me to a nice meal,

929
01:03:10,151 --> 01:03:11,851
and that she was bringing you along.

930
01:03:29,711 --> 01:03:30,841
Veronica...

931
01:03:37,181 --> 01:03:38,351
That name...

932
01:03:40,951 --> 01:03:42,551
The person who gave it to you
was your mother.

933
01:03:46,761 --> 01:03:47,761
And...

934
01:03:50,561 --> 01:03:51,691
that mother...

935
01:03:55,661 --> 01:03:56,701
is me.

936
01:04:01,341 --> 01:04:04,771
So, you found out.

937
01:04:13,681 --> 01:04:16,691
Mom...

938
01:04:24,491 --> 01:04:26,061
Mom.

939
01:04:32,001 --> 01:04:33,141
Let me just...

940
01:04:34,971 --> 01:04:36,571
Let me just hold you.

941
01:04:40,141 --> 01:04:42,811
Oh, my girl... My daughter...

942
01:04:48,351 --> 01:04:49,951
My daughter...

943
01:04:50,791 --> 01:04:51,891
My girl...

944
01:04:56,431 --> 01:04:57,561
My girl...

945
01:04:57,831 --> 01:04:59,131
Mom...

946
01:05:35,601 --> 01:05:38,001
(Recipe For Love)

947
01:05:38,401 --> 01:05:40,341
Mr. Park, are you one of
Director Baek's people?

948
01:05:40,901 --> 01:05:44,471
Min Seo, the English tutor for Ji Hu
and Se Ri. She's Se Ri's daughter.

949
01:05:46,581 --> 01:05:48,911
- Dae Han was having dumplings...
- Hey!

950
01:05:49,111 --> 01:05:51,451
- with his girlfriend.
- Did you see who she was?

951
01:05:51,511 --> 01:05:54,451
It was Dong Suk. Yang Dong Suk.

952
01:05:54,521 --> 01:05:56,851
You should have just denied it.

953
01:05:57,021 --> 01:05:59,291
We had to cross that bridge
sooner or later anyway.

954
01:06:00,061 --> 01:06:02,991
If my uncle finds out,
he might actually hit Mr. Gong.

955
01:06:04,139 --> 01:06:06,079
Dramaday.me
